                WikiProjekt Photography

                This list of immovable cultural monuments in the Old Brno part of the city district of Brno-střed in the city of Brno in the district of Brno-město is based on the Central list of cultural monuments of the Czech Republic , which, on the basis of Act No. 20/1987 Coll., on State Monument Care , is maintained by the National monument institute as the central organization of state monument care . The data are continuously refined, but may still contain a number of factual and formal errors and inaccuracies or be out of date.

                If some parts of the territory concerned have been separated into separate lists, references to these sub-lists should be given at the beginning of that list or at the beginning of the relevant section of the list.

                Žaček's family house ( Q38047872 )


                		ano
                   
                		48219/7-7534
                Memory catalog
                MIS                 		Old Brno Lipová 549/17
                49°11′39.44″ N , 16°34′56.61″ E                 		Villa, of which only: the front of the house. Architecturally and urbanistically valuable facade of a family house by Eduard Žáček.

                Note: The group of functionalist family houses also includes houses Lipová 233/20, 234/22, (235/23), 236/25, 248/43 in the Pisárky part of the Brno-střed district .
                Listed since March 11, 1988.

                Villa of Václav and Zdenka Pokorných ( Q38136689 )


                		ano
                   
                		48404/7-7720
                Memory catalog
                MIS                 		Old Brno Lipová 906/1, Zlutý kopec 537/1
                49°11′40.24″ N , 16°35′6.17″ E                 		Villa, of which only: facade. Valuable asymmetrically divided facade of a functionalist villa built in 1930–1931 according to a design by Jindřich Kumpošt.

                Note: MonumNet listed two descriptive numbers, the Memorial Catalog mentions only No. 537, on the other hand, only No. 906 is noted on the registration sheet. In RÚIAN, both addresses are focused on the same definition point. The house stands on Lipová Street, but No. 537 is assigned to Žlutý Kopec Street in RÚIAN.
                Listed since November 10, 1988.

                Waterworks complex on the Yellow Hill ( Q24352771 )


                		ano
                   
                		106360
                Memory catalog
                MIS                 		Old Brno Yellow hill, pp. 325, 326, 328, 329, 330
                49°11′44.18″ N , 16°35′27.81″ E                 		The waterworks complex is an impressive monument of the time of generous city building, reviving ancient archetypes of representative and at the same time utilitarian architecture.
                • brick reservoir from 1868–1876 with a fitting chamber from 1913, floating brick architecture of the oldest reservoir
                • brick reservoir from 1896–1900, floating brick architecture with a temple-like appearance
                • concrete two-chamber cistern with an armature chamber from the beginning of the 2nd decade of the 20th century, monumental, temple-like architecture
                • house of technical background, romantic historical building

                Listed since April 16, 2019.

                Own villa of architect Mojmír Kyselka ( Q33256468 )


                		ano
                   
                		103787
                Memory catalog
                MIS                 		Old Brno Tomešova 566/4a
                49°11′46.13″ N , 16°35′32.21″ E                 		Family house - architect Mojmír Kyselka's own villa. Functionalist terraced family house with mostly intact exterior and interior, imaginative layout, built-in furniture, setting in the terrain with elements of dynamic, organic architecture. The terraced family house is set into the slope on the side of the Yellow Hill in such a way that the eastern street facade is three-storey with direct access to both the basement and the ground floor via an outdoor staircase. The western facade to the garden is two-storey with direct access to the terrain from the 2nd floor. On the third floor there is a fronted outdoor terrace. Conceptually, it is a two-generation house with two apartments connected by two staircases. The five-axis east facade consists of four windows and an entrance in the basement. On the north wall of the loggia is a stone relief of a lion from the former restaurant At the Blue Lion in Staré Brno.

                Note: MonumNet was reporting what. 4
                Listed since 19 December 2009.

                Starobrno brewery and malthouse ( Q33256368 )


                		ano
                   
                		47997/7-7310
                Memory catalog
                MIS                 		Old Brno Mendlovo náměstí 158/20, Pivovarská 960/2, Hlinky
                49°11′27.41″ N , 16°35′33.31″ E                 		The former Starobrno brewery and malt house with a cellar. Today's appearance of the former brewery in Staro Brno (no. 158 and 960) is the result of structural modifications from 1872 on the site of the original monastery brewery. Three-winged building on an irregular floor plan. The south wing facing the square is divided into two tracts - a storey tract with a hall with windows facing the square and a five-story building of the former malt house with a pitched roof topped by a massive chimney. Interior spaces modernly adapted for the needs of a restaurant, social hall and brewery. On the northwest side, the area is protected by an approximately two-meter high plastered enclosure wall ending in a low gable roof. In the southeast, the site is opened by an approximately 1.5 m high terrace.

                Listed since February 22, 1988.

                Starobrno Monastery ( Q334311 )


                		ano
                   
                		23059/7-23
                Memo. catalog
                MIS                 		Old Brno Mendlovo náměstí 157/1, 419/2, 470/2a, Úvoz 419/1
                49°11′30.89″ N , 16°35′40.1″ E                 		Klášter Králové (area of ​​the Augustinian monastery, formerly the Cistercian nuns). One of the most historically and architecturally valuable monasteries in Brno, made up of a unique complex of Gothic and Baroque buildings, was founded in 1323 by Queen Eliška Rejčka on the site of an early medieval princely fort.
                • monastery - complex of buildings, No. 157, parc. 7/1
                • Church of the Assumption of the Virgin Mary, parc. 1
                • Orlovina No. 470
                • parish building No. 419
                • Marian column, former garden, park 5/1
                • circular pool, parc. 5/2
                • monument to Gregor Mendel, parc. 8
                • orangery (Mendel's greenhouse) - disappeared, parc. 8
                • apiary, park 15
                • garden, enclosure wall

                Listed since March 23, 1964.

                Letohrádek Mitrovských – Arena ( Q12033142 )


                		ano
                   
                		20932/7-39
                Memo. catalog
                MIS                 		Old Brno Veletržní 920/19
                49°11′18.46″ N , 16°35′20.56″ E                 		Letohrádek Mitrovských (Arena) with park. Park area with elegant small classicizing architecture from the period after 1779. Illusive wall paintings preserved in the interior.
                • summer house. A free-standing neoclassical building completed in 1794 as a summer retreat for the Mitrovský family.
                • staircase with terrace. The new construction of the terrace with a staircase developed according to the project of A. Jeřábková in the years 1977–1987. Functionally connected with its own summer house.
                • park. The remains of a larger park with a garden, established at the summer house at the end of the 18th century. The park is divided into a western part (next to the rear facade of the summer house) and an eastern part (next to the terrace in front of the entrance facade). The western part originally served as a farm background with an orangery, after the buildings were removed the area was landscaped, grassed and planted with lindens, there is also a group of pines and a solitary ash tree. The area is separated from Křížkovského Street and Veletržní Street with a sidewalk by a concrete wall. The eastern residential park is divided by sandy paths with concrete curbs, and there are mature trees and bushes on the grassy areas. The center of the composition is a circular area with greenery, on which the statue of Marta was secondarily placed.

                Listed since March 23, 1964.

                St Anne's Hospital ( Q12016624 )


                		ano
                   
                		26304/7-170
                Memory catalog
                MIS                 		Old Brno Pekařská 664/53 and 57, Anenská 664/15, Leitnerova
                49°11′26.86″ N , 16°35′54.02″ E                 		Hospital at St. Anne. A monumental Neo-Renaissance work by Theophilus von Hansen from the 1860s, situated in a park-like environment. The hospital complex was built on the site of the demolished buildings of the former Dominican convent of medieval foundation (beginning of the 14th century), which served as a hospital and nursing home since the Josephine reforms. The monumental building complex, centered around the trapezoidal courtyard, consists of the main front wing with a massive central elevation with an entrance vestibule and two other wings connected at a slight angle, from which two long courtyard wings extend at right angles and end in short wings connected at right angles. These wings are connected to each other by a ground-floor arcade corridor with the unique Neo-Palladian architecture of the institutional chapel of St. Anne in the middle. The elevated central risalit of the main wing is significantly pushed out into the courtyard area in the courtyard frontage, so it resembles a short wing.
                • Neo-Palladian Chapel of St. Anne's central arrangement on a Greek cross plan with a vestibule and a semicircular recessed apse arched with a conch, above the nave of a square plan is a tambour bearing a dome surmounted by an open lantern with a domed canopy. Tribunes on beams carried by Doric columns are inserted into the side naves.
                • The original park, which surrounded the hospital premises from the west and especially the east side and which was founded on the site of the original garden of the Dominican nuns, has largely disappeared today in the extensive construction of hospital buildings continuously built from the end of the 19th century to the present day.

                Listed since March 23, 1964.

                Pellicova 9 ( Q33256500 )


                		ano
                   
                		48161/7-7476
                Memory catalog
                MIS                 		Old Brno Pellicova 632/9

                 Kateřina Hirschová's rental house ( Q38136568 )


                		ano
                   
                		48000/7-7313
                Memory catalog
                MIS                 		Old Brno Husova 167/7, Pekařská
                49°11′32.75″ N , 16°36′17.45″ E                 		Due to its exposed location, Kateřina Hirschová's tenement house represents an important urban component of the Šilingrova náměstí area. Corner Neo-Renaissance three-storey palace-type house with two visually appealing facades, the side of which faces Husovy Street and the entrance faces Pekařské Street. The third floor is a modern addition from 1925. The corner is chamfered and a two-story rectangular bay window supported on consoles rises from it, at the top of which there is a balcony and below which there is a smaller entrance opening. A passage is pierced in the mass of the corner. The entrance facade is octagonal and is centralized by means of a shallow risalit, which includes three central axes and in the middle of which is broken a large, today mostly walled up entrance opening with a segmental arch. The side facade is octagonal, and most of its originally ground floor window openings have been extended to entrance openings or shop windows.

                Listed as a monument since 1 March 1988.
                Monument protection canceled on 26 January 2019.

                49°11′26.98″ N , 16°36′15.75″ E                 		Today, the single-storey classicist suburban house is the last surviving relic of the early 19th century terraced buildings of the street. The house is situated on an artificial terrace carved into the rocky side of the Petrova massif, about 2 m high above the level of Kopečná street running below it. In addition to the house, there is also a small front garden and a backyard behind the house on the terrace. The second, probably similar, wing enclosing the backyard in the northwest has been removed, leaving only a partially demolished brick wall, a prismatic projection on the northwest gable facade and a jammed step in the bedrock. The long street frontage to Kopečné street is smooth, six-axis.

                Zvonička s božími mukami (Q38136653)


                		ano
                   
                		48673/7-7989
                Pam. katalog
                MIS                 		Staré Brno v parku ve výseči ul. Křídlovická a Nové sady, parc. 1428/4
                49°11′9,37″ s. š., 16°36′12,58″ v. d.                 		Kaplička – zvonička s božími mukami. V brněnském kontextu unikátní drobná historizující stavba s neobvykle vkomponovaným sloupkem pozdně barokních božích muk, dominující prostranství parčíku při křížení ulic Nové Sady a Křídlovická. Barokní zděná sloupková boží muka obvyklého tvarosloví členěná pravoúhlými vpadlinami, v nichž se nachází mělké půlkruhově zaklenuté niky, završená bohatě profilovanou korunní římsou nesoucí stan, je velmi atypicky vkomponována do historizující architektury zvoničky ze závěru 19. století. Přízemí zvoničky je členěno 4 obloukově zaklenutými vstupy uzavřenými novodobými kovanými mřížemi a 4 mělkými nikami arkatury. Přízemí kapličky je avršeno profilovanou vyloženou římsou, na níž spočívá sloupový ochoz s toskánskými sloupky nesoucími nízký polygonální jehlan, ze kterého vyrůstá hranolová lucerna prolomená půlkruhově zaklenutými otvory. Lucerna je završena zalomeným polygonálním jehlancem završeným hrotnicí s makovicí.

                Křížová 16 (Q33256405)


                		ano
                   
                		103755
                Pam. katalog
                MIS                 		Staré Brno Křížová 97/16
                49°11′18,16″ s. š., 16°35′38,32″ v. d.                 		Měšťanský dům. Jeden z mála dochovaných představitelů nejranějšího horizontu klasicistní zástavby starobrněnského předměstí pochází z doby kolem roku 1800. Řadový jednopatrový trojkřídlý dům s hlavní východní uliční částí okapově orientovanou do prostoru Křížové ulice, s dlouhým v pravém úhlu navazujícím severním dvorním křídlem a s kratším křídlem jižním. Objekt se zachoval ve své hmotě a dizpozici, rovněž i v exteriéru a interiéru, s četnými původními architektonickými prvky a detaily (zaklenuté prostory v přízemí, některá dveře a okna, pozůstatky černé kuchyně aj.).

                Památkově chráněno od 30. října 2009.
